Just as important, 80% of the fresh vegetables eaten in the US from January to March each year comes from Florida. I hope @RepRooney will meet with farmers south of the Lake to learn what they are doing to protect Florida's environment. https://bit.ly/2TQCTMx

The value of agriculture to jobs, food supply, land management and our local government’s economy cannot be overstated. Florida’s famed agriculture industry employs over 2 million people and contributes more than $104 billion to our state’s economy each year.

Finger-pointing & hyperbole will not solve Florida's water issues. FL farmers are not a menace. They are doing more with less & achieving significant results. Phosphorus levels are down 50% from the late 1980s & growers have cut pollution by 56% every year for the last 20 years.
